Reasoning: The paper deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Word Embeddings, which are core topics in the field of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The use of machine learning techniques to predict individual's sense of humor and clustering humor ratings of multiple demographic groups falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of humor, which can be categorized under Social and Information Networks (cs.SD) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
